      <title>Re: Placate.. What's it good for???</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=8851#M8851</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;The thing about using placate to pull is, you usually don't need to pacify all the mobs in a room. Yes, if your puller shoots the first one, they might all 7 come. However, if you placate the second, that usually breaks the chain, and only the first comes. Since the higher level pacify spells (pacification and placate) are not line of sight, I often help pullers using placate, particularly if we have a paladin or warrior pulling. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;/pause 10, /assist tank&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;/cast x&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;/g placating a %T&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;then one hotkey for &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;/g %t pacified&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;and another that says &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;/g RESIST RESIST &amp;lt;a %t&amp;gt; has resisted placate.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
