      <description>&lt;br&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;hr&gt;dmanick wrote:&lt;br&gt;Placate is for when you got a rog giving you targets and using a bow / throwing weapons from a distance to pull.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If it goes bad they can always SoS.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;In other words its a spell that it's so situational that it's use has never come up for me yet in the last Hundreds of Hours of game play.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This spell ranks right up there with the innate undead invise AA and turn undead.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You have to get this spell for the progression of the other useful ones so guess it can collect dust like all the other spell ideas that got changed / nerfed or have no real use like:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;1. Extinguish Fatigue (I really would have like this spell to work currently, I got it in my spell book and it does nothing)&lt;br&gt;2. Wave of Tranquility (Who knows who did or did not get pacied good luck finding out)&lt;br&gt;3. Confidence :o (Hmm guess that extra 6 AC is worth the effort for just PAL and CLR's at less then half the duration and spell slots ahhh NOT!)&lt;br&gt;4. Banishment of Shadows (Pfft do I even need to explain this one, sure every CLR plans to have this mem'ed and know they type/name of mob the this works on)&lt;br&gt;5. Imbue "ECT" (I want all the ENC imbue after all doesn't a priest "Bless" items in real life???)&lt;br&gt;6. Silent Dictation (Refreash time that makes it good to reduce the number of spell slots.)&lt;br&gt;7. Calamity (Can you say Mana hog and ulta slow / low DPS)&lt;br&gt;8. Invise Undead only line (Undead only zones around for that 65 to 70 group and soloing that do not exist Chardok B don't count btw))&lt;br&gt;9. Sermon of Reproach :o (Big huge UD DoT Pfft 300 per tick what a joke.)&lt;br&gt;10. Resist's are rarely to never used either. Other classes have better.&lt;br&gt;11. Fear Get a mob to 20% and they run you got the same effect wheeeee. Now boy I want that starting earlier.&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As Alaana mentioned, placate is great for pulling - I used it all the time in OoW instances (dranik sewers and catacombs, for example) for single pulling in the over-populated rooms.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Let's review the rest of your list of "useless" spells.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Some of them truly are of little or no use - extinguish fatigue (which used to be useful before endurance changes), confidence and wave of tranquility come to mind.  Most of them, however, either were useful at their levels or in specific situations.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Specifically:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Banishment of Shadows was key for an encounter in Ssra.  Sure, it's not doing much today, but Luclin was a loooong time ago.  &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Calamity and Silent Dictation are useful in AE situations - you might not AE much, but that doesn't mean that these situations never arise.  I agree that Silent Dictation has a really long recast and I've never been a huge fan of that line of spells, but it's not completely useless.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;IVU can be very helpful in certain zones.  There are areas of The Nest that have high undead populations.  IVU is really good on one Txevu encounter (for one specific purpose).  It's also good for moving around in chardok B (even though that zone "doesn't count").&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Sermon of reproach (and the similar lines of spells) aren't remotely useful for grouping, but can be of some value while soloing (especially at lower levels - for example, can root/dot mobs in the grey).  I agree that at higher levels the damage/mana ratio on these spells makes them useless.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Fear just got a revamp, which increases it's usefulness to higher levels.  Without snare, fear doesn't help much for soloing, but it's great for duoing with a snare class at any level (cleric/ranger duos rock for fear kiting).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Imbue has a very limited value, that's true, but I kind of like this line of spells - each diety has a different connection with a particular stone and clerics of that persuasion can only imbue that particular stone.  There's nothing wrong with having a few utility spells directed toward a specific purpose.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Our resist line definitely needs an upgrade, but I still find myself casting the old ones from time to time (usually on specific encounters, like Fabled Kunark dragons, when no buffer of the appropriate class is around).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Of course, you neglected to mention the bestest spell of all, True North, which really is completely useless, given the nerf of sense heading.  I'm still waiting for the expansion that brings us Ancient: True North!!</description>
